results.title: Cover to Deathlok #4
results.description: The final battle! Deathlok is joined by Sunfire in his fight against Roxxon Oil!

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #1
results.description: Michael Collins is trapped in the body of a cyborg killer. Deathlok’s quest for his humanity begins here. Will this man-turned-cyborg find the human body he needs to be restored? Witness the strange saga, and origin, of Deathlok!

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #2
results.description: THE SOULS OF CYBER-FOLK PART 1 Guest-starring the X-Man, Forge! Deathlok squares off with the Capturebots after Forge and Misty Knight are nearly kidnapped. Why are the Capturebots after cyborgs? And will Deathlok and Misty Knight be able to save Forge?

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #3
results.description: THE SOULS OF CYBER-FOLK PART 2 Will Deathlok be able to save Misty Knight from the clutches of Doctor Doom? A battle to near-death ensues between a cyborg and a master of mystical arts! This is a can’t-miss conflict you have to see to believe!

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #4
results.description: THE SOULS OF CYBER-FOLK PART 3 Deathlok loses his mind to a deadly “Cyber-Folk”. Vision of the Avengers and the unusual Ruby Thursday join the fray!

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #5
results.description: After his stand-off with Doc Doom, Deathlok assembles the Doombusters! Who are the heroes committed to the cause of taking Doom out? And will the team be able to unite for their common cause? Featuring Wolverine, Jubilee, Forge, and Storm of the X-Men, plus the Fantastic Four!

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #6
results.description: SIMILAR MACHINES PART 1 Deathlok finds that he has more in common with the Punisher than he thinks, when Frank Castle enters a conflict between Deathlok and Silvermaine. Will Deathlok be able to protect his son, embroiled in his own trouble, from Silvermaine’s gang?

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #7
results.description: SIMILAR MACHINES PART 2 Punisher and Deathlok  chasing a common enemy. Punisher finds that he is short on mercy, while Deathlok struggles to maintain his humanity.

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #8
results.description: Deathlok faces Death! Who will stop at nothing to ensure Deathlok’s permanent end? An explosive conclusion that will leave you reeling!

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #9
results.description: Deathlok the Demolisher is back in town! Deathlok makes a triumphant return to doing what he does best- destroying! Plus, what happens when Deathlok encounters Ghost Rider? Too much violence! Guest-starring the Spirit of Vengeance in “Nightmares of Vengeance”!

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #10
results.description: Deathlok and Ghost Rider in a fight to the death! Will Michael Collins be able to escape the wrath of Johnny Blaze? Watch the two heroes struggle under the mind control of Nightmare!

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #11
results.description: Michael Collins breaks into his Main Factory Complex. But why does Deathlok break into Stark Prosthetics too? Michael Collins continues his quest for a human body! Plus, introducing High-Tech!

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #12
results.description: BIOHAZARD AGENDA PART 1 Deathlok’s grip on humanity becomes even more tenuous when he flies into a berserker rage. Will Michael Collins be able to reign himself in? And who will suffer if he loses all control?

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #13
results.description: BIOHAZARD AGENDA PART 2 Deathlok reunites with his family! Michael returns to his wife Tracy only to be greeted with a cold reception from her relatives. What shocking news will Tracy Collins reveal? And will Deathlok be able to restore his relationship with his family?

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #14
results.description: BIOHAZARD AGENDA PART 3 Deathlok will stop at nothing to live again as a human man. But what strange force is preventing his end goal? And could this be the resurrection of John Kelly, the first Deathlok?

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #1
results.description: Weird science meets bio-mechanized warfare in this gritty series starring Marvel’s mighty cyborg! Deathlok, half-man, half-robot, has escaped the inner sanctum of S.H.I.E.L.D. With his consciousness trapped inside six year old Billy Bailey, will Deathlok see the completion of his human form? A new saga for a new Deathlok begins here!

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #2
results.description: The empty shell of Deathlok continues his rampage across America, and now he’s hitting up Vegas! Will Nick Fury, and an elite task force of S.H.I.E.L.D., be able to leave Deathlok dead in his tracks? Plus, Billy Bailey begins the journey that will reunite his cyborg body to his human mind!

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #3
results.description: Billy Bailey walks through the mine fields of a decimated Las Vegas. Deathlok continues his mindless rampage without reprieve. If Nick Fury and his elite team can’t disable Deathlok, young Billy Bailey, and the rest of the nation, will suffer. Will Deathlok ever be whole in body and mind?

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #4
results.description: Who is the Clown in the Circus of Crime? Meet one of Marvel’s strangest, and perhaps least funny, mercenaries. What does the Clown wish to prove? And is he as skilled at taking down cyborgs as he is at taking lives? Nick Fury reaches a decision on the containment of Deathlok.

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #5
results.description: The transformation of Jack Truman into Deathlok laid out in full! How did Jack Truman become S.H.I.E.L.D.’s most dangerous weapon? And what part of himself did he lose in the process?

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #6
results.description: The finishing touches on Deathlok’s cyborg body complete! What will Deathlok do to test out his new abilities? But before Deathlok can get settled in his new form, he must eliminate a growing third-world threat!

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #7
results.description: Deathlok taps into his remaining humanity when he meets with his sister. Will Jack Truman ever feel the unification of body and mind again? Plus, an attack from the Serpent Society turns a happy reunion into a dangerous one!

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #8
results.description: Everyone wants a piece of Nick Fury, dead or alive! Deathlok is recruited by Dum Dum Dugan to locate Fury, while the Clown receives similar orders from his higher-ups. Which mercenary will reach Fury first? He who gets the spoils…decides the fate of Nick Fury!

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #9
results.description: Deathlok is in a frenzy to reach Nick Fury before the Clown does. Will Jack Truman’s mission prove successful? In the seedy underbelly of Los Angeles, Deathlok seeks answers about Nick Fury’s whereabouts. But what else will Deathlok uncover in this hotbed of crime?

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #10
results.description: Trapped in a web of political intrigue, Deathlok and the Clown face off in the name of democracy. What dirty secrets about a Presidential hopeful have been unearthed? And will Deathlok be able to defeat a mercenary dead set on his death?

results.title: Cover to Deathlok #11
results.description: The shocking conclusion to Jack Truman as Deathlok! In the final act, Ringmaster’s plot in becoming President may become reality. Will Nick Fury and his agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. be able to uphold the American way? Deathlok faces a health crisis when his body begins rejecting its cyborg parts. Could this be the end of Jack Truman the Deathlok, and a new beginning for Jack Truman the man?

results.title: Cover to Deathlok Annual (1992) #1
results.description: Four Deathlok stories combined in one issue! In his first annual, Michael Collins faces some harsh truths about his human family. Deathlok discovers Harlan Ryker’s journal. Could this discovery be the key to becoming a human once again?

results.title: GALACTUS THE DEVOURER (1999) #1
results.description: Reunited with his paramour, everything is going fine for the Silver Surfer, until the new herald known as Red Shift arrives! The warning has arrived and all must fear his dark arrival! Galactus, the Devourer Of Worlds, is headed towards Earth... and we're on his menu! This intense exploration of the dreaded destroyer of planets blows the lid off the major cosmic questions of the Marvel Universe, such as: What is the secret reason for the existence of Galactus (that was hinted at in FANTASTIC FOUR #262)? Why did Galactus choose a Herald? More specifically, why did he choose Norrin Radd and change him into the Silver Surfer? Why was it vital that the Surfer defied and broke away from his master? Why has everything that has ever happened to the Surfer led to this adventure? And what is the Surfer's ultimate purpose?

results.title: cover to GALACTUS THE DEVOURER (1999) #2
results.description: The Devourer of Worlds has gone mad, and Earth's on his menu! The Silver Surfer and Alicia Masters rocket into space to stop Galactus, only to be attacked by the planet eater's latest and deadliest herald: Red Shift! And even if they can defeat him, will they return in time to save our world from becoming a smoking husk?!

results.title: cover to GALACTUS THE DEVOURER (1999) #3
results.description: Galactus is prepared to consume the Earth, and even the power of the Avengers, the Fantastic Four and more may not be enough to stop him! You'll never believe the shocking ending, or the new beginning it unleashes!

results.title: cover to GALACTUS THE DEVOURER (1999) #4
results.description: Silver Surfer: once again the herald of Galactus?! In the aftermath of last issue's bombastic battle with the planet eater, the Earth's heroes witness the rebirth of one of the Devourer's former heralds...the Silver Surfer?! And things go from bad to worse as the Surfer leads the hungry Galactus straight for the homeworld inhabited by his former love, Mantis!

results.title: cover to GALACTUS THE DEVOURER (1999) #5
results.description: The epic cosmic adventure continues with guest stars The Kree, The Shi'ar, The Imperial Guard, The Starjammers, The Fantastic Four and The Avengers! The entire universe trembles before the might of Galactus, a god gone mad! In order to save Earth, a reluctant Silver Surfer has once again become the herald of Galactus! And to make matters worse, the Surfer is leading him directly to the Shi'ar homeworld!

results.title: cover to GALACTUS THE DEVOURER (1999) #6
results.description: Virtually every heavyweight hero stars in this planet-shattering conclusion! The Avengers, the Starjammers, the Imperial Guard, the Fantastic Four and the Silver Surfer make their last stand to save the Shi'ar homeworld! If they succeed in destroying Galactus, the universe will be saved...or will it?!

results.title: cover to Gambit (1997) #1
results.description: A shooting star has fallen to Earth in the form of a woman, and it’s up to Gambit to protect the celestial body from those who wish to abuse her power.

results.title: cover to Gambit (1997) #2
results.description: Despite being seriously injured, Gambit must find Anielle before it’s too late!

results.title: cover to Gambit (1997) #3
results.description: Gambit and Anielle flee the country as the evil Stoker chases them down!

results.title: cover to Gambit (1997) #4
results.description: The final confrontation between Gambit, Anielle and Stoker!  Will Gambit and the personified star survive this conflict?

results.title: cover to Generation X Annual (1995) #1
results.description: Cordelia Frost wants to join the Hellfire Club as White Queen, no matter what the cost is! And what secrets has M been hiding from the team?
